0/1680773213347?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=O3HAtFA6bCTN4apWtWKyB2XAX_he2GWTUO5MmJxBSbk", "peopleAlsoViewed/24/public_identifier": "nguyễn-hải-yến-2057b5141", "peopleAlsoViewed/24/url": "https://linkedin.com/in/ACoAACJ3weUBatlXNqCYpHrJ3sqhvTiojgblrrM", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/entity_urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAFoNkYBdc_uLGQbkPaa8Nj-sZtSXOaHIZs", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/first_name": "Laura", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/follower_count": "2617", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/headline": "APAC Managing Director at PURPLE", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/last_name": "Derry Southwood", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/premium": "false", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/profile_picture": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4E03AQGN5rzwT__XqQ/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/0/1727866988650?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=tW8-9Qsig5fZoVsF38o4Wmbwj6HgUymFBv4Jx-2TTFc", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/public_identifier": "laura-derry-southwood-45aaa57", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/url": "https://linkedin.com/in/ACoAAAFoNkYBdc_uLGQbkPaa8Nj-sZtSXOaHIZs", "publicIdentifier": "hillda2024", "recommendations/0/context": "David worked with Lusida Chistina on the same team", "recommendations/0/date": "August 30, 2020", "recommendations/0/description": "I had the pleasure to recruit and work with  Lusida at the Bintan Lagoon Resort (Indonesia), she was part of my food and beverage team who re positioned and relaunch banqueting, catering and events successfully  targeting MICE business from international markets.   (Russia, Vietnam, New Zealand and Singapore).\n\nLusida has a can do attitude, extremely guest focused, detail orientated, pleasant personality and willingness to learn and adapt in order to improve performance of herself and her department.   Lusida was a pleasure to work with, she developed an in depth understanding of departmental profit and loss whilst teaching her team how to service and exceed guest expectations.  \n\n Lusida was equally comfortable working as Manager on duty, or handling guest requests/complaints.  Her positive relaxed manner and natural ability to speak with anyone endured her to guests and employees.  She has attention to detail and trains her team with passion, understanding and humour.  I have observed her career develop with interest she has a passion for the industry and a natural ability to train and develop people that benefits her department/business.  I have no hesitation in recommending Lusida for positions within the hospitality industry.", "recommendations/0/name": "Lusida Chistina Sihombing", "recommendations/0/subtitle": "Senior Specialty Restaurant Manager @ Wyndham Hotels & Resorts", "recommendations/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/lusida-chistina-sihombing-57892759/", "recommendations/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAxq0GwBuYz-SNH3qrdl4whxC2WVzcIq9oA", "recommendations/1/context": "David managed Hue directly", "recommendations/1/date": "August 21, 2020", "recommendations/1/description": "Ms Hue was my Personal Assistant for two years, office manager overseeing our Executive Office with two locations in Dalat and HCMC, she also was responsible for marketing coordination with our third party contractors, handling all correspondence, discussions and contractual documents that was much appreciated on both sides. When dealing with dual language discussions/documents it is so easy to make mistakes or loose content or intention through translation discrepancies, Ms. Hue ensured that clear, concise and organized handling of all related local vendors, which allowed win/win achievements on both sides through her approach all vendors were able to deliver in a timely manner and to the standards required, saving time, improving turnaround, reducing frustration and developing long term relationships with the vendors. \n \nMs. Hue has a natural customer service orientation, calm under pressure, able to handle projects, events, financial and multiple tasks whilst not loosing site of the strategic objectives. She also has natural ability to learn whilst doing and her positive attitude, learning abilities, professional and consistent attitude to work was very much appreciated when handling both Vietnamese or International clients or owners with excellent command of the English language and with international exposure through family members complemented by an excellent educational background. Moreover, being meticulous in her work, very adaptable, resourceful, never waiting to be asked and being able to operate with autonomy and independence and a level of empowerment which supports her own development.\n \nI have watched her career grow within the time she worked with me and also since leaving in November 2017, she commenced work with Colliers International I am pleased to see how her reliability, dedication and self-learning continue to personally develop. \n \nI have no hesitation in recommending Ms. Hue, she will be an asset to any employer who can utilize a very capable, adaptable , self-learner with an ability to handle complex and detailed tasks in dual language and who is highly organized and focused whilst having a pleasant and calm personality that delivers repeated consistency.   Should the opportunity arises, I would work with Ms. Hue again in a role suited to her new skill set and abilities\n", "recommendations/1/name": "Hue Hoang, PMP", "recommendations/1/subtitle": "Project Manager", "recommendations/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/lily-hoang-73605838/", "recommendations/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAfWjxoB0HWzeikNm2xQUQl5lo38uVgHvoI", "recommendations/2/context": "David managed Norbert directly", "recommendations/2/date": "August 20, 2020", "recommendations/2/description": "Norbert has a passion for Hospitality, is meticulous with detailed planning which he gained over many years of military service.  Using his skills he focuses his teams and together  achieve results through focus, clarity and understanding.  Norbert is a results orientated and an excellent strategic planner. His customer service and focus delivers exemplary service results and employee satisfaction.  He develops the talent around him, teaches service excellence, and has demonstrated consistent improved results in each of his positions.  I have seen this personally as I worked with Norbert twice in my career, initially hiring him in 2006 from Europe for position in Courtyard Kuwait as housekeeping manager.   I saw a manager with front desk and duty manager experience who could expand on his military background and improve efficiency in operations combined with excellent customer and problem resolution skills and a calm demeanor.\nThe results he achieved in this role improved efficiency, service quality and consistency as well as departmental cooperation.  He taught  English to housekeeping team specifically related to job focused so that team members with limited skills in English could improve their understanding of job related tasks increasing the retention rate and reducing the turnover.  \n\nNorbert gained through this opportunity the expertise and added foundations that would establish his career path from that point in time to excel at senior roles in management.\nI worked with Norbert again in 2011 - 2013 when he was a member of my senior team in Vietnam and he was Rooms Division Manager for The Reverie Saigon (LHW).   Norbert  was involved in all pre-opening planning and follow up on critical path items under his responsibility, whilst also maintaining operational oversight of rooms division in one of our other 5 star hotels in the group.  The 40 floor tower was opened successfully on January 2013 after hiring of 500 staff which were successfully on boarded.  \n\nHis career growth from Front Desk Manager, Housekeeping Manager through Rooms Division Manager to EAM/Resident Manager is down to Norbert ability to self develop, teach others and delivery consistent results for his team and financial goals of the business.   I am very proud of his achievements and how he teaches, mentors others whilst self developing.  He is an asset to any owner/operator of branded or independent property and I have no hesitation in recommending him for senior roles in hospitality he is very adaptable and reliable i would gladly work with Norbert again in the future if the opportunity arises.", "recommendations/2/name": "Norbert Meyer", "recommendations/2/subtitle": "Resort Manager", "recommendations/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/norbert-meyer-35275314/", "recommendations/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAL1Py4Be5FGjwcqiemFRm0Cer9je3DoZx0", "recommendations/3/context": "David managed Teodor directly", "recommendations/3/date": "July 30, 2018", "recommendations/3/description": "I had the pleasure of both recruiting and working with Teodor at the Courtyard by Marriott (Kuwait City) and watching his career grow from that of FOM to General Manager.   \n\nI am so pleased of his accomplishments and growth in the industry since our initial paths crossed.  \n\nTeodor is an exceptionally talented General Manager and business leader.  Teodor is an asset to any organisation that he works with, highly focused and diligent, exceptional leader/trainer/mentor whilst possessing analytical and creative skills.  Teodor's knowledge of the industry and departments in it, combined with his passion for the people in it (guest and employee) is personal approach rarely seen in todays industry and is unique and refreshing. \n\nTeodor  understands how to create an environment that fosters creativity and business performance. \n\nTeodor is a highly motivated senior manager, who brings passion, fun, creativity and knowledge to his every day implementation of service excellence in all that he manages.  \n\nTeodor is a great mentor, develops and invests personal time into his teams and creates an atmosphere of development, learning and his teams excel and have developed into new roles through his guidance and teaching.\n\nI am very proud to have seen his career grow and am pleased that i was able to provide some guidance to this talented young man who has a passion for the industry and people seldom seen in todays business.  \n\nPeople make our business successful and he truly understands this factor and implements it in his every day work.  i will continue to watch his career grow with interest.\n\nI do not hesitate to recommend Teodor as General Manager or similar senior roles, he is a talented young man whom I will watch with interest over the coming years.  Should the opportunity arise in the future i will certainly hire Teodor again and wish him the best of luck in his future development.\n", "recommendations/3/name": "Teodor Ardeleanu", "recommendations/3/subtitle": "Founder of the KiTrain Method", "recommendations/3/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/teodor-ardeleanu-3382aa8/", "recommendations/3/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAF3h1wBGXq96YXESDVJ_KhLDYQuShScuGQ", "recommendations/4/context": "David managed Bambang directly", "recommendations/4/date": "July 30, 2018", "recommendations/4/description": "I had the pleasure of working with Mr. Bambang in Indonesia, I recruited him as my Director of Finance through recommendations from a colleague who worked with Bambang before in Vietnam.  Mr. Bambang was a perfect choice for the role, his personal knowledge of all financial issues, standard accounting practises and implementations of these across the resort was invaluable.   \n\nHis depth of knowledge is not restricted to financial, he also has a firm understanding of the entire hospitality industry from Human Resources and team work development to knowledge of all Legal issues domestically and also internationally to Sales and Marketing of the business,\n\nBambang has a depth of knowledge and expertise that makes him a truly rounded senior manager who has a pleasant personality, is a mentor to his team and others, he also provides the Executive Committee informed information on their departments and business performance overall.   Bambang is an asset to any organisation he works with.\n\nBambang was able to support me and I him, ensuring that financial compliance was implemented across the resort and issues addressed speedily.  \n\nHis in depth knowledge of the legal frame work concerning hospitality business was also an invaluable to me whilst working in his home country of Indonesia.  \n\nBambang is professional and was a valuable member of my senior team.  He is diligent, hard working, pays attention to the details without losing oversite of the larger picture affecting the business.    He possess a great sense of humour and humility, is highly read and informed and always adding to his knowledge through self learning and extensive reading.\n\nBambang is a great mentor, trusted confidant and over the years since we worked together we have maintained constant contact, he is a highly regarded friend and professional sounding board on all matters financial and systems related.  \n\nI would not hesitate to recommend him to any organisation looking for a senior financial manager, he is a true asett and has the ability to explain the complicated nature of finance, in a way that every senior member of the team can understand.\n\nI personally would rehire Bambang in the future should the opportunity arise and I have no hesitation in recommending him for roles in the business and hospitality industries, whether as a full time role, or as interim manager, or consultant to audit and setup businesses that need an independant audit of proces and systems.  Bambang is a true professional and one that will bring value to your organsiation.\n", "recommendations/4/name": "Bambang F.X.", "recommendations/4/subtitle": "Managing Partner at Hospitality Consultant", "recommendations/4/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/bambang-f-x-6017355/", "recommendations/4/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAD_fCEBdsm7bMOP_KIUiO1VSTzzmDFrXPk", "recommendations/5/context": "David managed Markus directly", "recommendations/5/date": "November 17, 2013", "recommendations/5/description": "Markus worked with me at WMC where he oversaw the change management of an engineering department which had previously never done preventative maintenance, or project management or resolving problems. \n\nDuring our time working together we identified operational issues in most systems, and procedures and set about implementing Standards SOPS, operational efficiencies and resolving long standing problems in the building maintenance and operations.\n\nMarkus is highly talented engineer, works well with teams, and very good at solving problems and identifying the route cause to prevent re occurrence, a good leader and leads from the front with hands on approach to work.   \n\nDuring our time together we reduced expenditure, reviewed all serviced contracts and commenced the renovation work of the Windsor Plaza Hotel Rooms, Kitchens, Public corridors, AHU and Air conditioning in the rooms and ballroom and meeting space, whilst also completing the laundry renovation of the property.\n\nMarkus is a dedicated and highly skilled chief engineer whom I recommend for any future projects/work and I look forward to working with him again at some point in the future.\n\nDavid A. Hill", "recommendations/5/name": "Markus Reumer", "recommendations/5/subtitle": "Director of Engineering at Mandarin Oriental Palace Lucerne", "recommendations/5/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/markus-reumer-7a440051/", "recommendations/5/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAArqhGwBfXLnjd8mr0yb52NG_Z7-Hpve5JA", "recommendationsReceived/0/context": "Norbert reported directly to David", "recommendationsReceived/0/date": "August 16, 2020", "recommendationsReceived/0/description": "I had the pleasure working  with David twice so far in my career 1st  2006 to 2009 when he was Director of Rooms at Courtyard by Marriott in Kuwait City and 2nd when he was Group General Manager at WMC Vietnam from 2011 to 2013, which manages several 5-star properties including The Reverie Hotel Saigon as member of  Leading Hotels of the World.\nDavid hired me 2006 as housekeeping manager when I came from front office operations. It was this out of the box offer which allowed me  learn and excel to become front office manager then  rooms division manager and resident manager which I partially achieved through his believe in me and  guidance. \nIn both positions i have experienced David is an great leader  ambitious, exemplary and passionate senior leader, who is highly intelligent, across wide range skill sets he is results driven, develops talent and business  development focused,  he is extremely creative when it comes to adding value for customers which in return increased shareholders value significantly.\n\nDavid is working extremely pro-active, highly organized and structured  \n\nHis strong, modern and innovative leadership, his undivided attention to details, his motivating and inspiring team spirit as well as his personal coaching and development activities made David exceeding business goals and owner expectations on a regular basis. He and his teams received multiple awards for the contributions done in both locations.\n\nTherefore, I do not have any hesitations recommending David to any organisation which would like to become excellent in operation and goal achievement.\n", "recommendationsReceived/0/name": "Norbert Meyer", "recommendationsReceived/0/subtitle": "Resort Manager", "recommendationsReceived/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/norbert-meyer-35275314/", "recommendationsReceived/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAL1Py4Be5FGjwcqiemFRm0Cer9je3DoZx0", "recommendationsReceived/1/context": "David was Eric Lynge's client", "recommendationsReceived/1/date": "August 16, 2020", "recommendationsReceived/1/description": "I would recommend David for any senior role in the hospitality, resort, club and golf industry. I worked together with David at the Dalat at 1200 Golf and Country Club in Dalat, Vietnam from 2015-2017 when he held the role as General Manager of this foreign owned project. During that time, there was a renovation of 9 holes and expansion to 18 holes on the golf course, a development of real estate plan for the area and membership and real estate marketing plan in development. The Korean LPGA also staged an event at the resort in 2016. I was able to observe David's interaction with ownership group and his staff.  His years of management experience with the Marriott Group as well as several projects in Vietnam and SE Asia lead to a very results oriented view which he clearly communicates in both corporate and operational environments. He observes cultural differences and adapts accordingly while keeping his eye on the main result which is success in the project. He is clearly adaptable to most situation and clear and level headed in all situations. He also maintains a positive world view and demeanor which encourages all who interact with him. \n", "recommendationsReceived/1/name": "Eric Lynge  李瑞明", "recommendationsReceived/1/subtitle": "Strategic Advisor - Sports & Media Asia Pacific | Golf Industry Specialist | Board-Level Experience | Conference Speaker/Moderator | Fractional Leader", "recommendationsReceived/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/eric-lynge/", "recommendationsReceived/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAACAgcBIWP9lXX0A-UDDIkQ6d74STXZEEw", "recommendationsReceived/2/context": "Teodor worked with David on the same team", "recommendationsReceived/2/date": "August 16, 2020", "recommendationsReceived/2/description": "David is one of the best leaders I have ever met and worked with in my entire life. David has a broad education and people skills. He can see beyond the little details and understand the big picture of any situation. David is business driven while taking care of the team. Rarely you find a smart leader like him.\nTeodor", "recommendationsReceived/2/name": "Teodor Ardeleanu", "recommendationsReceived/2/subtitle": "Founder of the KiTrain Method", "recommendationsReceived/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/teodor-ardeleanu-3382aa8/", "recommendationsReceived/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAF3h1wBGXq96YXESDVJ_KhLDYQuShScuGQ", "recommendationsReceived/3/context": "Hue reported directly to David", "recommendationsReceived/3/date": "August 14, 2020", "recommendationsReceived/3/description": "Mr. Hill was my direct manager for two years and I was his personal assistant, I've improved my own performance and learned to understand business and customer expectations.  His guidance and training to the team showed patience, understanding and required confirmation to ensure we understood the meanings.   In Asia we do not like loose face so would seldom say I do not get it. However his calm demeanour and passion to ensure we understood resulted in improvements to business performance.    \nHe has many years experience in managing teams and business and his can do attitude and work ethic was an inspiration.   His mindset can inspire the whole organization, he leads by example and hands on at the guest end of the business.   I developed attention to detail and adapted yes is the answer how can we help.  I was able to adapt my own experience and develop incredibly my career path which saw me achieve new position and utilise my experience I learned. \nDavid is a rare combination of patience, integrity and knowledgeable in Hospitality his expertise in construction/ management/ strategy and investment amazed us. I learned a lot and was a  pleasure to work with him. Being a teacher and mentor to many, I saw how he guided not only myself but many others so customers received good service he is hands on and with service staff and guests. “A great leader creates and nurtures other leaders” is  my favourite saying to describe David who mentored myself and others. David truly believes in service and business development and to achieve these goals details and attention to details with training are the key.   Financial goals come when basics 