('Adnan YÜCEL', 'Adnan', 'YÜCEL', '🌟 Luxury Hospitality Leader 🌟 Empowering Diverse Teams Across Cultures 🌟 Advocate for Wellness, Sustainability & Purpose 🌟 Expert in Revenue & Turnaround 🌟 Creating Authentic, Heartfelt & Memorable Guest Experiences', 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/adnanyucel', 'adnanyucel', $${"about": "With over three decades of global leadership in luxury hospitality, I am passionate about crafting guest experiences that are not only memorable, but deeply meaningful. Currently serving as General Manager at InterContinental Chiang Mai The Mae Ping, part of IHG Hotels & Resorts, I lead with a people-first philosophy rooted in empathy, purpose, and performance.\n\nMy career has taken me across continents—from the ancient streets of Türkiye to the vibrant energy of China and Indonesia, the cultural richness of Ghana and Saudi Arabia, and the dynamic hospitality landscapes of the United States and Thailand. Along the way, I’ve held pivotal leadership roles with renowned brands such as Swissôtel, Hilton, Fairmont, Accor, Six Senses, and IHG—each shaping my understanding of excellence, innovation, and cultural intelligence.\n\nAt different international brands, I gained foundational experience in guest relations, operations, and service delivery—learning to balance consistency with creativity across diverse markets. These years taught me the significance of brand integrity and adaptability while managing stakeholder expectations and leading diverse teams.\n\nMy leadership at Six Senses Uluwatu and Six Senses Kaplankaya reinforced my passion for wellness, sustainability, and experiential hospitality. There, I led strategic transformations, oversaw large-scale refurbishments, and developed empowered, multicultural teams who delivered thoughtfully curated guest journeys.\n\nIn my current role with IHG, I lead a team committed to excellence while spearheading property refurbishment and turnaround initiatives. Whether streamlining operations, designing guest-centric strategies, or mentoring rising talent, I focus on delivering measurable results that are backed by purpose.\n\nFluent in the language of people, purpose, and performance, I believe in leadership that is both visionary and compassionate. Sustainability and wellness aren’t just industry pillars—they’re personal values that guide every decision.\n\nHaving traveled extensively and lived in eight countries, I bring a unique cross-cultural perspective to every role I take on. This global lens helps me understand what truly resonates with people—from guests to teams to partners—and how to foster environments where everyone thrives.", "addressCountryOnly": "Thailand", "addressWithCountry": "Chiang Mai, Thailand", "addressWithoutCountry": "Chiang Mai", "backgroundPic": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4D16AQF5VFZnrFtGOQ/profile-displaybackgroundimage-shrink_350_1400/B4DZYj8CxBG4AY-/0/1744359668317?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=cmFTrudzRvEduMo75iHzOl7BmFAOxwblWzxPC3Zx4ec", "companyIndustry": "Hospitality", "companyLinkedin": "https://www.linkedin.com/company/ihghotels&resorts/", "companyName": "IHG Hotels & Resorts", "companySize": "10001-0", "companyWebsite": "http://www.ihgplc.com", "connections": "20777", "creatorWebsite/0/category": "COMPANY", "creatorWebsite/0/url": "www.intercontinental.com/chiangmai", "currentJobDuration": "1 yr 2 mos", "currentJobDurationInYrs": "1.17", "educations/0/period/endedOn/month": "0", "educations/0/period/endedOn/year": "1994", "educations/0/period/startedOn/month": "0", "educations/0/period/startedOn/year": "1990", "educations/0/subtitle": "French Language and Literature", "educations/0/title": "Istanbul University", "educations/1/period/endedOn/month": "0", "educations/1/period/endedOn/year": "2009", "educations/1/period/startedOn/month": "0", "educations/1/period/startedOn/year": "2008", "educations/1/subtitle": "Certificate, General Managers Leadership Development Program", "educations/1/title": "Gallup University", "educations/2/