ldives @ IHG Hotels & Resorts | Driving all strategic HR dimensions realistically and practically.", "peopleAlsoViewed/23/last_name": "Khaneng", "peopleAlsoViewed/23/premium": "true", "peopleAlsoViewed/23/profile_picture": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C4D03AQHPgwvvdYoLtg/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/0/1655016919684?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=Iva3FKgjV3EjfqyM-_XqRaT1zYi6QcRoRA2uJh2lP-o", "peopleAlsoViewed/23/public_identifier": "saudikhaneng", "peopleAlsoViewed/23/url": "https://linkedin.com/in/ACoAAAqKzSQB8kLpaSo_6d8giCm-vW2pxJrBQBU", "peopleAlsoViewed/24/entity_urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAvg2rAB32L4kUG0XqFm4I6FbmeSUQHBCFU", "peopleAlsoViewed/24/first_name": "Sabrina", "peopleAlsoViewed/24/follower_count": "1972", "peopleAlsoViewed/24/headline": "General Manager at InterContinental Hua Hin Resort", "peopleAlsoViewed/24/last_name": "Hofstetter", "peopleAlsoViewed/24/premium": "false", "peopleAlsoViewed/24/public_identifier": "sabrinahofstetter", "peopleAlsoViewed/24/url": "https://linkedin.com/in/ACoAAAvg2rAB32L4kUG0XqFm4I6FbmeSUQHBCFU", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/entity_urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAUPVrYBj2Ci4ptSaIgIdXOsK9jec_T2TDg", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/first_name": "Hasan Fahri", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/follower_count": "0", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/headline": "Radisson Blu Hotel and Conference Center, Niamey owned by FB Group, General Manager, Hotelier, 6 Sigma - Green Belt, Skal Ankara President", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/last_name": "B.", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/premium": "false", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/profile_picture": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4E03AQFRkDTk1t7pmQ/profile-displayphoto-crop_800_800/B4EZ2q58nyH0AI-/0/1776688812385?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=08hn7z1kdviAQiQEFQfhs8u6c7vO7QGwu8wCsZGJ_T0", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/public_identifier": "hasan-fahri-b-b0651a24", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/url": "https://linkedin.com/in/ACoAAAUPVrYBj2Ci4ptSaIgIdXOsK9jec_T2TDg", "profilePic": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D5603AQHkAf5N-UpvMg/profile-displayphoto-crop_800_800/B56Zy0QEM1IsAI-/0/1772550637890?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=y1oIa2MvmxF3uJvIpVLzr9B84fVBDohXHtv0UYxxcR8", "profilePicHighQuality": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D5603AQHkAf5N-UpvMg/profile-displayphoto-crop_800_800/B56Zy0QEM1IsAI-/0/1772550637890?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=y1oIa2MvmxF3uJvIpVLzr9B84fVBDohXHtv0UYxxcR8", "publicIdentifier": "adnanyucel", "recommendations/0/context": "Adnan was senior to Anara but didn't manage Anara directly", "recommendations/0/date": "July 19, 2025", "recommendations/0/description": "It is with great pleasure that I recommend Ms. Anara Atraubaeva for any role she may desire. During her tenure as Kids Club Manager at Six Senses Kaplankaya, Anara consistently demonstrated outstanding dedication, warmth, and professionalism in caring for our youngest guests.\n\nHer enthusiasm was palpable—from organizing creative and educational activities to attentively engaging with children from diverse cultural backgrounds. With her international experience and natural ability to connect with both children and parents, Anara played an integral role in elevating guest satisfaction and contributing to memorable family experiences.\n\nShe is hard-working, dependable, and carries an uplifting energy that resonates across teams and guests alike. Any organization fortunate enough to have her will find in Anara not only a passionate team player, but also a true ambassador of heartfelt hospitality.", "recommendations/0/name": "Anara Atraubaeva", "recommendations/0/subtitle": "Groups,Conferences & Events | Luxury & Lifestyle", "recommendations/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/anara-atraubaeva/", "recommendations/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAC5KW0IBi9FMSBRtNaSacZ5YM8bdTn4fa1U", "recommendations/1/context": "Adnan was René J. M.'s client", "recommendations/1/date": "June 21, 2025", "recommendations/1/description": "I’ve had the pleasure of knowing René for nearly two decades, and in that time, I’ve come to deeply admire his professionalism, integrity, and vision. As the founder of Top Hoteliers, René has built one of the most respected executive search firms as first one specialized in Greater China and then Southeast Asia, and the Pacific—combining sharp market insight with an unmatched personal commitment to his clients and candidates.\n\nWhat makes this especially meaningful for me is that I’ve seen his journey unfold firsthand—from the early days of building his network to becoming a trusted name in hospitality recruitment. His ability to maintain authenticity, warmth, and clarity of purpose, even in the most demanding of environments, has left a lasting impression on me both personally and professionally.\n\nRené isn’t just a leader in his field; he’s a loyal friend, a sharp thinker, and someone who genuinely elevates those around him. I’m proud to recommend him and Top Hoteliers without reservation.", "recommendations/1/name": "René J. M. Schillings 诗林", "recommendations/1/subtitle": "Senior International Experienced Hospitality Recruitment from Asia since 2004. reaching a global audience", "recommendations/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/rené-j-m-schillings-诗林-85b71a9/", "recommendations/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAG1PUcBuFjSxhj2GsEjsZwEu1t2vKlPr4c", "recommendations/2/context": "Adnan was HASAN BARIS's client", "recommendations/2/date": "August 8, 2024", "recommendations/2/description": "Barış is an amazing person carrying a lot talents. \n\nBesides being involved/leading in many social and commercial organizations, he is actively working as a guide too. \n\nHe is the perfect person to guide you throughout the history of old Istanbul. \n\nWe had a chance to meet him via our mutual friends and had the pleasure to take the old town tour with him including Topkapı Palace, Basilica Cistern and many more.\n\nBe ready to get surprised with his unusual/hard to find anywhere else stories while enjoying the empire era Istanbul.\n\nWe wanted to get our daughter to see the history with right guide as it was her first time visiting these treasures because she was grown up away from Istanbul.\n\nWe wouldn’t find any better person than him as he mixes humor with knowledge which gives a great pleasure to listen to.\n\nHis enthusiasm and love for the job is impeccable.\n\nWe can’t wait to dive into a new historical adventure with him again.\n\nMany thanks again for the super tour Barış !\n\nAll the best !\n\nAdnan Yücel", "recommendations/2/name": "HASAN BARIS PARTAL", "recommendations/2/subtitle": "“The best story hasn’t been told yet” Local History Cross-cultural interpretation Turkish Sign Language Fact, Event, Space and People in Constitutional Monarchy (1908-1923) of İstanbul", "recommendations/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/hasanbarispartal/", "recommendations/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAV9Vn8Bzx8R1XJ1SKYfzLGD_g7US5TfrFk", "recommendations/3/context": "Adnan managed Randolf Edward directly", "recommendations/3/date": "June 14, 2022", "recommendations/3/description": "We worked with Randolph about 2 years during entire the worst period of covid-19 pandemic. He has shown himself as a reliable and hard working colleague, a good friend in tough times. He performed all the tasks which he was given. He is a true -can do man- who never says No. he would always find solution to overcome challenges. He’a been a great -swiss knife- who could handle anything.\nI have enjoyed very much working with him and I would love to work with him again if an opportunity arises in future again. He is a true hotelier and a pillar for his hotel. I wish him all the best in his future endeavours. ", "recommendations/3/name": "Randolf Edward Maisie", "recommendations/3/subtitle": "Kenfix supervisor at Mövenpick Hotels & Resorts", "recommendations/3/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/randolf-edward-maisie-91480b222/", "recommendations/3/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAADgBT2ABYnQEWC46_lVxMHpv0wb8bjbg80g", "recommendations/4/context": "Adnan managed Esener directly", "recommendations/4/date": "April 18, 2018", "recommendations/4/description": "I worked with Esener during my tenure at Swissotel Ankara with great pleasure.\nHe has been always supportive, very efficient, fast decision maker, cooperative with whomever he was in touch with.\nEsener was always thinking out of the box, was always been a team player, very professional and helping other departments with their challenges too.\nEsener is a very analytical guy who pursue his targets till the very end. He never gets tired of additional tasks and always sees them as an opportunity to grow.\nHe is resilient person under stress. He has worked with me where/when we had the most powerful political figures visiting and staying with us, celebrities were regular and business was booming. We have been busy in every aspect. Esener didn't think just like a regular Finance Director but he also supported when needed extra management hand in other areas and he also represented the management during my absence in many occasions.\nI am sure that Esener will excel in his hospitality career as he always does and will have no issue achieving his targets and future objectives.\n", "recommendations/4/name": "Esener Saygin", "recommendations/4/subtitle": "Vice President Finance Operations, AEMEA, Raffles & Fairmont Hotels and Resorts", "recommendations/4/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/esenersaygin/", "recommendations/4/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAcJ2ZMBTTAcPBnehPcGrwGcidYNdNTjT1c", "recommendations/5/context": "Adnan worked with André on the same team", "recommendations/5/date": "March 17, 2015", "recommendations/5/description": "We worked with Andre over the same period at Wanda Hotels & Resorts, during the first few years of the company. Andre has a solid background in hospitality industry with great experience, enthusiastic and warm personality and proactive leadership skills. We opened our hotels almost at the same period and Andre is already is on her third successful hotel in the group. It's been a great pleasure to know Andre and his teams are always lucky to have him as their leader.", "recommendations/5/name": "André Erasmus", "recommendations/5/subtitle": "Group COO - Auriga International | Global Hospitality & Management Consulting | Operational Excellence, Growth & Value Creation", "recommendations/5/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/andrejerasmus/", "recommendations/5/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAFE3fIBC8WWX2RiDj3Q7s1kauqIxVEKQ2E", "recommendations/6/context": "Adnan managed Amy directly", "recommendations/6/date": "August 22, 2014", "recommendations/6/description": "Amy has a great personality and professional mind. She's been a great support to us during my tenure at Swissotel Foshan. She was always energetic, positive with her lovely smile around the hotel. She was a role model with her attitude. She is a perfect training manager and has a bright future in her career. I wish her all the best and hope to work together again.", "recommendations/6/name": "Amy Li", "recommendations/6/subtitle": "Sofitel Foshan - Talent & Culture Manager", "recommendations/6/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/amy-li-70697868/", "recommendations/6/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAA5hnPYBluJxGV43QrcOWLORWItSiHu_R0s", "recommendations/7/context": "Adnan managed Diana directly", "recommendations/7/date": "July 18, 2014", "recommendations/7/description": "Diana is a great talent in hospitality industry or any industry she would like to pursue in her career. \n\nShe worked with me as my personal assistant at Sofitel Luxury Hotels and climbed up to revenue manager position at Wanda Hotels & Resorts with her nonstop ambition, enthusiasm, energy and hardwork for her responsibilities. \n\nDiana takes her responsibilities very seriously and she won't give up until she reaches her target and finishes her task. Her commitment is unique. \n\nShe is a very reliable colleague and a friend who won't let you down no matter what. \n\nShe will work with you like your right arm and will complete you as a professional. I worked with her almost 3 years in different properties and always admired her character. \n\nShe is analytical, detailed, programmed and always great with new technologies. \n\nShe's reliable, honest, ethical, serious with a great sense of humor. I am absolutely sure that she will be a great leader with her skills and wish her the best in her future ambitions.", "recommendations/7/name": "Diana Wen", "recommendations/7/subtitle": "Revenue Management", "recommendations/7/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/diana-wen-982a433a/", "recommendations/7/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAhXNbIBW6wG0MZ92s2MqZh0BKX3jV44O3M", "recommendations/8/context": "Adnan managed Huascar E. directly", "recommendations/8/date": "April 19, 2013", "recommendations/8/description": "Huascar is a great, fun guy to work with. He's been a hardworking and a professional team member. He got along well with guests, colleagues and superiors alike. I am sure that he'll add a great value to his work wherever his career leads him to. Needless to say that he was always punctual and honest. I wish him all the best as he surely deserves it.", "recommendations/8/name": "Huascar E. Gomez (Rick), MSA", "recommendations/8/subtitle": "Area Director of Finance", "recommendations/8/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/huascar-e-gomez-rick-msa-18286a13/", "recommendations/8/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAALL-nIBz1p8V8bxd8RAuHnG_SwXRFs8B3g", "recommendations/9/context": "Adnan managed Michael directly", "recommendations/9/date": "April 19, 2013", "recommendations/9/description": "Michael is a great hotelier with a professional discipline combined with a sense of humor which makes him a highly respected leader in our industry. In his capacity as DoFB at Sofitel Dongguan Humen Oriental, he managed to motivate a very big team in such a short term and succeeded to bring good results. His German discipline, punctuality and hardworking style flavored with his Asian experience made an incredible touch and example for his team. He knows how to communicate and embrace a team very fast. He had hundreds of team members because of the size of the hotel but he managed them in a way that they all felt like a family as he transformed himself to the local culture within a day. I have transferred back Michael to China from Estonia, knowing that his Guangdong and Beijing experience would help me to speed up to the process of re-shaping the F&B department with his extensive culinary and service experience. His detail oriented, results driven professional. I am sure that Michael will excel in whatever capacity he desires for and will become a great GM in short time. I will have no hesitation to work with Michael again if wishes so and I am sure that he will always add a tremendous value to his business. He’s a precious colleague and a friend.", "recommendations/9/name": "Michael S.", "recommendations/9/subtitle": "Hotel General Manager | P&L Leadership, Asset Stabilization & Operational Excellence | Luxury & Independent Hotels | Asia & Europe", "recommendations/9/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/michael--schumacher/", "recommendations/9/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAJ75SgBreBTTFom3EK-gwLfMqTRe00-GtQ", "recommendations/10/context": "Adnan worked with AbdelRaouf on the same team", "recommendations/10/date": "December 23, 2011", "recommendations/10/description": "AbdelRaouf is a true professional with great passion for his work. He's able to perform very well under pressure. During my time in Makkah, I observed his abilities during the opening of Raffles Makkah and pre-opening stage of Fairmont Makkah under extremely hard conditions. His experience and enthusiasm for excellence makes him a great manager in our industry. I am pretty sure that he's capable for more success stories in future.", "recommendations/10/name": "AbdelRaouf Sawalmeh", "recommendations/10/subtitle": "CFO/ COO at ASQ Holding LLC | Ras Al Khaimah", "recommendations/10/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/abdelraoufsawalmeh/", "recommendations/10/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAALlSNwBdSiUqspqLbOo94SrO78UD3IRWnk", "recommendations/11/context": "Adnan was senior to Rose but didn't manage Rose directly", "recommendations/11/date": "September 10, 2011", "recommendations/11/description": "Rose is a passionate young girl who devotes her self to her job and takes responsibility of your department carefully. She's dependable, loyal, hard working, punctual and very strong team leader. During challenging periods of our hotel with 100% occupancy every day, she never complained a single time about the work load. She works overtime with full power and always shows a good example of taking the business seriously to new comers. With high turnover of China hospitality industry, she always kept the backbone of her department very strong. Her team members admired her and followed her as a good leader.\nI am lucky that I had Rose running guest services department which allowed us to have a smooth service and high standard at guest services department. \nI have full confidence to recommend Rose to every future employer and I wouldn't hesitate to hire her in future again. I am certain that she would be successful wherever she desires to work no matter how challenging the environment is in any managerial position.", "recommendations/11/name": "Rose Huang", "recommendations/11/subtitle": "Guest Service Manager at Swissotel Foshan", "recommendations/11/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/rose-huang-72410733/", "recommendations/11/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAb070wB9MiDYoP6abr4qQrlMwH-eQs_VOo", "recommendations/12/context": "Adnan was senior to Harun but didn't manage Harun directly", "recommendations/12/date": "July 3, 2010", "recommendations/12/description": "Harun has a great personality who has the balance of managing people with his soft but detail oriented method. He's always kind and caring about every single member of his team but also never loosing his sight on high service quality and profitability at the same time.\nI enjoyed working with Harun during my time at Hilton Adana & Hilton Mersin and I believe that we achieved great successes with his strong role in our team.\nI am sure he adds value whereever he is and whoever he's working with and he's a great chance for people surrounding him as well as his property/ies.\nHarun is one of the people that I would always love to work with again with joy and passion.", "recommendations/12/name": "Harun Dagli", "recommendations/12/subtitle": "Commercial Asset & Hotel Performance Speacialist|Driving GOPGrowth|FTE Efficiency|Unlocking hidden profit in Hotel Operations", "recommendations/12/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/harundagli/", "recommendations/12/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAAJgsYB9b7PMZlfrcw4b75JEfzyTyTHAfo", "recommendations/13/context": "Adnan reported directly to Stephen Phillips", "recommendations/13/date": "May 16, 2010", "recommendations/13/description": "Mr. Phillips is one the greatest team leaders that I have worked with. As well as his professional knowledge, he's also a great motivator.\n\nI had the pleasure to work with Mr. Phillips when I was Revenue Manager at Swissôtel Dalian and he's been a great supporter of yield management.\n\nHe had a very large team of sales & marketing and always knew how to lead every single person in that team. He knew also how to treat everyone equally and enjoyed sharing his leisure time with colleagues.\n\nAs he's working as consultant for some time, unfortunately none of our new hotelier colleagues will enjoy working with him but there are still many opportunities for investors to benefit from his experience, knowledge and great personality.", "recommendations/13/name": "Stephen Phillips Lord of Ballinaboy", "recommendations/13/subtitle": "Owner, CEO Asia Hospitality Security / CEO HMA / Managing Director, Asia Pacific Lotan HLS & Defense", "recommendations/13/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/stephen-phillips-lord-of-ballinaboy-8452195/", "recommendations/13/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAADr-nUBsKIqq0yVMyaC5T4WpltZBIQu0BE", "recommendations/14/context": "Adnan worked with Abdurrahman  on the same team", "recommendations/14/date": "May 16, 2010", "recommendations/14/description": "Abdurrahman is a great finance director with an extensive experience and knowledge in his field. He's detail oriented, very careful and analytical thinker. When we worked with him at the same company and being both in cluster positions, we experienced a lot of challenges together in our both hotels due to difficult times such as gulf crisis etc. but we succeeded at the end with the power of him being a valuable team player too. I'm sure that he will add an incredible value where ever he works at and whom ever he works with. Needless to say that he's a great asset for Hilton. I wish him best of luck in his bright future.", "recommendations/14/name": "Abdurrahman  T.", "recommendations/14/subtitle": "Cluster General Manager @ Adana & Mersin HiltonSA - 2016 Connie Award Winner at DT by Hilton Malatya & Connie Award Winner for 2022 - 2023 at Mersin Hilton. Integrity Award winner MEA & Türkiye for the year 2023.", "recommendations/14/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/abdurrahman-t-8ab51a18/", "recommendations/14/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAOi1YMBgNeFEvDgwQZdgchL3QDvYzue7kM", "recommendationsReceived/0/context": "Anna-Pearl reported directly to Adnan", "recommendationsReceived/0/date": "November 11, 2023", "recommendationsReceived/0/description": "Adnan has exemplarily leadership skills. The following stand out:\n\nSupportive\nTeam player\nTeam Development\nEmpathy \nCalm in challenging situations \nFriendly but firm.\n\nAdnan always looks for ways to ensure a positive atmosphere within the working environment and ensures growth opportunities are given to deserving employees.\nHis calm nature even in challenging situations brings the best out of his team.\nIt was a real pleasure working with him.", "recommendationsReceived/0/name": "Anna-Pearl Azanlekor", "recommendationsReceived/0/subtitle": "People,Talent & Culture Strategist | Strategic Human Resource Management | Training & Development | Labour Relations | Alternative Dispute Resolution | Change Management | International Business", "recommendationsReceived/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/anna-pearl-azanlekor-1472913b/", "recommendationsReceived/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAhn6IcBt76sO6DpVT64K_iP6FdY3Vdfdc8", "recommendationsReceived/1/context": "Esener reported directly to Adnan", "recommendationsReceived/1/date": "May 15, 2020", "recommendationsReceived/1/description": "He has very good personality and business ethics. I was very happy to support him as director of finance in Swissotel Ankara where we had very successful period. Human/team care, target focus, team success, motivation, ethics and networking are the worlds which can be used to introduce him shortly...", "recommendationsReceived/1/name": "Esener Saygin", "recommendationsReceived/1/subtitle": "Vice President Finance Operations, AEMEA, Raffles & Fairmont Hotels and Resorts", "recommendationsReceived/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/esenersaygin/", "recommendationsReceived/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAcJ2ZMBTTAcPBnehPcGrwGcidYNdNTjT1c", "recommendationsReceived/2/context": "Diana reported directly to Adnan", "recommendationsReceived/2/date": "March 5, 2017", "recommendationsReceived/2/description": "I am so grateful to have Mr. Yucel as mentor as I set forth in hospitality industry during which was an inspiring journey of the early part of my career.\nHe is a General Manager with entrepreneur spirit who focuses on striving for the business result, in the mean time leading his team members in pursuing of their career and personal life successes.\nIt is also surprised to see expat talent like him with such strong senses of local market insights which ensures every business decision delivering best outcome. Great leadership and his attention to valuable details enabled him continually driving for the outstanding KPI result in a high level of team morale.\nWhat enlightened me the most was his excellent interpersonal and social networking skill which makes him always succeed in maintaining the business connection, owning company and government relationship, of course being a popular General Manager among the associates.", "recommendationsReceived/2/name": "Diana Wen", "recommendationsReceived/2/subtitle": "Revenue Management", "recommendationsReceived/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/diana-wen-982a433a/", "recommendationsReceived/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAhXNbIBW6wG0MZ92s2MqZh0BKX3jV44O3M", "recommendationsReceived/3/context": "Adnan was senior to Arden but didn't manage Arden directly", "recommendationsReceived/3/date": "February 25, 2017", "recommendationsReceived/3/description": "l worked with Mr.Adnan Yucel when l was a Director of MICE in Intercontinental Foshan in 2015. he is a very professional and experienced general manager and a   kindly gentleman person who devote to luxury hotel brand standard to hotel and always fully support S&M.Working for him was a really pleasure. ", "recommendationsReceived/3/name": "Arden Ye", "recommendationsReceived/3/subtitle": "Director of Sales and Marketing", "recommendationsReceived/3/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/arden-ye-b9088b35/", "recommendationsReceived/3/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAdtSNwBZSiB--LBzM-b1h4tp4yPMMbAFVY", "recommendationsReceived/4/context": "André worked with Adnan on the same team", "recommendationsReceived/4/date": "March 9, 2015", "recommendationsReceived/4/description": "Adnan was a fellow General Manager at the Wanda Hotels and Resorts group and we both opened our hotels over the same period. I was most impressed with Adnan’s professionalism and decisive leadership skills. He is very well respected at all levels of the organization and the travel trade. He exceeded all expectations and successfully opened a world-class 5star hotel under very challenging conditions.  ", "recommendationsReceived/4/name": "André Erasmus", "recommendationsReceived/4/subtitle": "Group COO - Auriga International | Global Hospitality & Management Consulting | Operational Excellence, Growth & Value Creation", "recommendationsReceived/4/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/andrejerasmus/", "recommendationsReceived/4/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAFE3fIBC8WWX2RiDj3Q7s1kauqIxVEKQ2E", "recommendationsReceived/5/context": "Michael reported directly to Adnan", "recommendationsReceived/5/date": "April 19, 2013", "recommendationsReceived/5/description": "In the short Period i had the pleasure to work together with Adnan i got to know him as a very passionated and profesional, detail oriented, true Hotelier who is always capable to handle any upcoming Issue in a serious yet realistic way. Even under the most challenging circumstances Adnan stays cool, calm and profesional giving always a very good example for his Managers as well as the complete Team. I would describe his management Style as modern and people oriented which leads Adnan to be a very well respected Leader within the Management and the Rank and File Team. \nAs a Leader he is always happy to share his extensive Hospitality knowledge with his Team, giving clear and detailed structured advices and encouraging the individual to work independent and reach top Results at any time. \nI am confident that Adnan brings great Value to any Property and its Teams  leading them to new levels of Succes. \nI would not hesitate to work with him again if there is a possibility in the Future.", "recommendationsReceived/5/name": "Michael S.", "recommendationsReceived/5/subtitle": "Hotel General Manager | P&L Leadership, Asset Stabilization & Operational Excellence | Luxury & Independent Hotels | Asia & Europe", "recommendationsReceived/5/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/michael--schumacher/", "recommendationsReceived/5/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAJ75SgBreBTTFom3EK-gwLfMqTRe00-GtQ", "recommendationsReceived/6/context": "AbdelRaouf worked with Adnan on the same team", "recommendationsReceived/6/date": "December 23, 2011", "recommendationsReceived/6/description": "Although it was a short period of time, Adnan managed to leave a quick impression on how professional he is, keen to adapt new environments and work under different circumstances", "recommendationsReceived/6/name": "AbdelRaouf Sawalmeh", "recommendationsReceived/6/subtitle": "CFO/ COO at ASQ Holding LLC | Ras Al Khaimah", "recommendationsReceived/6/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/abdelraoufsawalmeh/", "recommendationsReceived/6/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAALlSNwBdSiUqspqLbOo94SrO78UD3IRWnk", "recommendationsReceived/7/context": "Alp Mahir reported directly to Adnan", "recommendationsReceived/7/date": "August 26, 2011", "recommendationsReceived/7/description": "It is real pleasure to get to know Mr. Yucel and I was lucky enough to be a part of his team at Swissotel Ankara for two years. He is a person of distinction and dignity whom I took as a role model with his extensive knowledge, strong social relations and kind personality. He always gives equal opportunity to people, shares his knowledge and let them further improve. Creating an environment with mutual trust and honesty he encourages creativity and sets up for success. I sincerely wish him the best in the future.", "recommendationsReceived/7/name": "Alp Mahir Akyuz", "recommendationsReceived/7/subtitle": "General Manager | Accor", "recommendationsReceived/7/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/alpakyuz/", "recommendationsReceived/7/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAIKJssBQzX7vFHbqzMvz3LVdRc_aipursQ", "recommendationsReceived/8/context": "A. Tayfun was senior to Adnan but didn't manage Adnan directly", "recommendationsReceived/8/date": "August 23, 2011", "recommendationsReceived/8/description": "During his work life in Hilton Adana & Hilton Mersin: \n\nAdnan was a well organized person, a good communicator, had practical problem solving skills, works under full pressure and never effected negatively.  \n\nHe created a large number of close contacts within partner companies, agencies, press and guest profiles.  That helped us to improve our relations and warm up relations to divert any kind of business to our hotels. \n\nHis people management and relation skills helped him to set up a stronger sales team and close contacts within customers. I believe that he has achieved a good result during that period and helped Hilton to continue to have a high profile.\n\nIt was good to work with a professional person like him.", "recommendationsReceived/8/name": "A. Tayfun Dogan", "recommendationsReceived/8/subtitle": "Retired Human Resources Manager( I'm not looking for any job)", "recommendationsReceived/8/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/a-tayfun-dogan-0674976/", "recommendationsReceived/8/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAEjmI8B-ZiRzBsa5d9EPe5SH00ilaKwZ-M", "recommendationsReceived/9/context": "Atilla reported directly to Adnan", "recommendationsReceived/9/date": "January 2, 2011", "recommendationsReceived/9/description": "I have worked together with Adnan Yucel as my General Manager direct reporting to him for 2 years at Swissôtel Ankara. Adnan is a true professional with strong human relationship not only with his team but as well with all business clients, tourism industry. It was a total pleasure and lot of learning points and expriences shared by him with me and his team to develop the team members. Having many local & international working exprience has given extensive vision to me and to the team. I wish all the best for his new position and new challenges which he always like to cope with challenges and ends up with success stories.", "recommendationsReceived/9/name": "Atilla Aytun", "recommendationsReceived/9/subtitle": "Radisson Blu Hotel Ankara General Manager", "recommendationsReceived/9/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/atilla-aytun-42b30612/", "recommendationsReceived/9/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAKJbuMB65yw8yERMdc3xnZikqwe7yUCyPQ", "recommendationsReceived/10/context": "Adnan was senior to Harun but didn't manage Harun directly", "recommendationsReceived/10/date": "June 29, 2010", "recommendationsReceived/10/description": "Adnan manages to wrap strategic thinking and detail orientation into one highly motivated package; making him an inspiration to others and always a pleasure to work with. Adnan is results driven and consistently challenges himself, his team and his peers to do better; at the same time, he is adept at recognising individuals and offering support when needed. His open and approachable style, coupled with his breadth of industry experience, ensures Adnan is a trusted and valued colleague often sought out for honest advice. I have enjoyed working with Adnan and would welcome the opportunity to do so again.", "recommendationsReceived/10/name": "Harun Dagli", "recommendationsReceived/10/subtitle": "Commercial Asset & Hotel Performance Speacialist|Driving GOPGrowth|FTE Efficiency|Unlocking hidden profit in Hotel Operations", "recommendationsReceived/10/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/harundagli/", "recommendationsReceived/10/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAAJgsYB9b7PMZlfrcw4b75JEfzyTyTHAfo", "recommendationsReceived/11/context": "Abdurrahman  worked with Adnan on the same team", "recommendationsReceived/11/date": "May 17, 2010", "recommendationsReceived/11/description": "I have to say that it was great pleasure for me to work together with Adnan. He was one the best person & manager I have ever worked together. He added value to our business during his working, especially during the Gulf Crise. His relation was perfect, not only with his Team and other managers in the Hotel, with the businessmen in the city (Adana & Mersin) as well. Still they remember and ask Adnan.", "recommendationsReceived/11/name": "Abdurrahman  T.", "recommendationsReceived/11/subtitle": "Cluster General Manager @ Adana & Mersin HiltonSA - 2016 Connie Award Winner at DT by Hilton Malatya & Connie Award Winner for 2022 - 2023 at Mersin Hilton. Integrity Award winner MEA & Türkiye for the year 2023.", "recommendationsReceived/11/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/abdurrahman-t-8ab51a18/", "recommendationsReceived/11/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAOi1YMBgNeFEvDgwQZdgchL3QDvYzue7kM", "recommendationsReceived/12/context": "Stephen Phillips managed Adnan directly", "recommendationsReceived/12/date": "May 16, 2010", "recommendationsReceived/12/description": "Adnan Yucel was an associate of mine and in his position as Revenue Manager of Swissotel Dalian, Adnan reported to me when I was Director of Marketing & Sales. Adnan was a hard worker, detail oriented, targeted and with clear objectives. He established the concept of Revenue Management at Swissotel Dalian and worked closely, coordinating the activities of the Sales, Reservations and Front Office functions. \n\nI would highly recommend Adnan for any position which he might choose to tackle. He is without doubt one of the most intelligent, clear thinking and capable colleagues with whom I have had the fortune to work.", "recommendationsReceived/12/name": "Stephen Phillips Lord of Ballinaboy", "recommendationsReceived/12/subtitle": "Owner, CEO Asia Hospitality Security / CEO HMA / Managing Director, Asia Pacific Lotan HLS & Defense", "recommendationsReceived/12/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/stephen-phillips-lord-of-ballinaboy-8452195/", "recommendationsReceived/12/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAADr-nUBsKIqq0yVMyaC5T4WpltZBIQu0BE", "recommendationsReceived/13/context": "Oswaldo worked with Adnan on the same team", "recommendationsReceived/13/date": "September 27, 2009", "recommendationsReceived/13/description": "Adnan is an outstanding and hard-working human being; he is highly motivated and driven by his strong commitment to providing exceptional service; a real leader in our industry.\nI had the pleasure of working with Adnan in Boston almost a decade ago and I have nothing but praise for him.\nAdnan will always excel and I would highly recommend him.\n\nOswaldo Mera", "recommendationsReceived/13/name": "Oswaldo Mera", "recommendationsReceived/13/subtitle": "Co-Founder & Managing Director", "recommendationsReceived/13/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/oswaldo-mera-86599b/", "recommendationsReceived/13/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAAlVA0BZnnN5Pwras8ugR_ONndtVjMNhUw", "skills/0/title": "Team Leadership", "skills/1/title": "Executive Management", "skills/2/title": "Financial Analysis", "skills/3/title": "Business Analysis", "skills/4/title": "Management", "skills/5/title": "Revenue Management", "skills/6/title": "People Management", "skills/7/title": "Challenge Management", "skills/8/title": "Operations Management", "skills/9/title": "Owner Relationship", "skills/10/title": "Crisis Management", "skills/11/title": "Team Building", "skills/12/title": "Team Motivator", "skills/13/title": "Analytical Abilities", "skills/14/title": "Forecasting", "skills/15/title": "Budget Preparation", "skills/16/title": "Sales and Marketing", "skills/17/title": "IT Management", "skills/18/title": "Delegation", "skills/19/title": "Executive Positioning", "totalExperienceYears": "26.3", "totalRecommendationsGiven": "15", "totalRecommendationsReceived": "14", "urn": "ACoAAACGu7EBBhtFnsc6ygVyzKsp8IG1TqqjQF8", "volunteerAndAwards/0/description": "Çukurova Hotel Association, a member of Turkish Hotels Federation.", "volunteerAndAwards/0/duration/months": "0", "volunteerAndAwards/0/duration/years": "0", "volunteerAndAwards/0/end_date/month": "9", "volunteerAndAwards/0/end_date/year": "2005", "volunteerAndAwards/0/industry": "Social_services", "volunteerAndAwards/0/is_current_position": "false", "volunteerAndAwards/0/organization": "Çukurova Hotel Association", "volunteerAndAwards/0/role": "Secretary General", "volunteerAndAwards/0/start_date/month": "6", "volunteerAndAwards/0/start_date/year": "200